-- Sub-Sahara Africa Stocks Report: Guaranty Trust, Kakuzi Shares Are Active
-- B y   V i n c e n t   N w a n m a   a n d   J o h n s t o n e   O l e   T u r a n a
-- 2010-12-08T16:32:15Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-08/sub-sahara-africa-stocks-guaranty-trust-kakuzi-are-active.html
The  Nigerian Stock Exchange All-Share
Index  advanced 0.2 percent to 24,681.17 at the 2:30 p.m. close
in Lagos, according to the exchange.  Namibia’s  FTSE/Namibia Overall Index  snapped a five-day
rally, falling 0.1 percent to 843.42 at the 5 p.m. close in
Windhoek. Mauritius’s  SEMDEX Index  added 0.1 percent to 1,937.14
at the 1:30 p.m. close in Port Louis. The  Ghana Stock Exchange
All-Share Index  declined less than 0.1 percent to close at
7,081.65 at 1 p.m. in Accra. Kenya’s  Nairobi All-Share Index 
climbed 0.1 percent to close at 78.68 by 3 p.m. in Nairobi.  The following shares rose or fell in sub-Saharan Africa,
excluding South Africa. Stock symbols are in parentheses.  Guaranty Trust Bank Plc  (GUARANTY NL), Nigeria’s third-
biggest lender by market value, gained to the highest level in a
month after Fitch Ratings affirmed the bank’s B+ rating with a
stable outlook. The shares increased 1.2 percent to 16.7 naira.  Kakuzi Ltd.  (KKZI KN), a Kenyan tea and fruit producer,
rose for the first day in three after tea prices advanced at the
world’s largest auction of the leaves in Mombasa. The stock
added 3.2 percent to 80 shillings.  To contact the reporters on this story:
 Vincent Nwanma  in Lagos via Johannesburg at 
 vnwanma@bloomberg.net 
 Johnstone Ole Turana  in Nairobi at 
